comments.text: determine which intent to handle with - conversation, knowledge (search memory), task (lots of llm calls) or ignore (dont do anything)
store the incoming chat message from user
try to find existing embedding for input, otherwise create one
add embedding to the input event to use in different sub-graphs
determine "interest" - should the agent respond to this input?
debug indicator to the user that the agent is ignoring
if the agent has a response, respond to user and store the response as an event
create an embedding of agent response and store it as an event
debug response to let the user know what the intent was
